========,1,preface.
Benton is a borough in Columbia County, Pennsylvania, United States.
The population was 824 at the 2010 census.
It is part of the Bloomsburg–Berwick Micropolitan Statistical Area.
========,2,Geography.
Benton is located in northern Columbia County at (41.196144, -76.383354).
It is surrounded by Benton Township, a separate municipality.
According to the United States Census Bureau, the borough has a total area of , of which is land and , or 2.96%, is water.
Fishing Creek, a south-flowing tributary of the Susquehanna River, runs through the eastern part of Benton.
